title: Webb 2016
description: Over the past few months thousands of concerned Americans from across the political spectrum have urged me to run for President.  A constant theme runs through these requests.  Americans want positive, visionary leadership that they can trust.  They’re worried about the state of our economy, the fairness of our complicated multicultural society, the manner in which we are addressing foreign policy and national security challenges, and the divisive, paralyzed nature of our government itself.  In short, they’re worried about the future.  They want solutions, not rhetoric.
